# State Management

Use the smallest state scope that can support the feature.

## Local State

Use component-local state for local UI concerns such as open menus, selected tabs, temporary form fields and transient loading state.

## Composables

Use composables for reusable behavior, derived state and shared interaction logic. Keep composables small and testable.

## Stores

Use stores only for shared application state needed across distant components or routes. Avoid storing data globally just to avoid passing props.

{% if use_pinia -%}
Pinia is enabled for this project. Place stores in `app/stores/` and keep actions focused on application state transitions.
{% else -%}
Pinia is not enabled. Add it only when shared application state justifies it, and record the decision if it changes project architecture.
{% endif -%}

## Server State

Server data should be loaded through Nuxt data utilities or server routes. Do not duplicate server state globally unless there is a clear caching or coordination need.
